Sentencas: Perovskite-type La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 (delta)(LSGM) is synthesized by conventional solid state reaction.
Titulo: Behavior of strontium- and magnesium-doped gallate electrolyte in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Its phase composition, microstructure, relative density, and oxygen-ionic conductivity are investigated.
Titulo: Behavior of strontium- and magnesium-doped gallate electrolyte in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Tubular electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are prepared with the LSGM as electrolyte and gadolinia doped ceria (GDC) mixed with silver as anode.
Titulo: Behavior of strontium- and magnesium-doped gallate electrolyte in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SOFCs are operated with Fe-loaded activated carbon as fuel and ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: Behavior of strontium- and magnesium-doped gallate electrolyte in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A typical single cell gives a maximum power density of 383 mWcm(2) at 850 degrees C, which is nearly 1.3 times higher than that of the similar cell with YSZ as electrolyte.
Titulo: Behavior of strontium- and magnesium-doped gallate electrolyte in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A stability test of 72 min is carried out at a constant current density of 210 mA cm(2), with a fuel utilization of 60%, indicating that LaGaO3-based electrolyte is promising to be applied in direct carbon SOFCs (DC-SOFCs).
Titulo: Behavior of strontium- and magnesium-doped gallate electrolyte in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells
